# KMP coding standards

> **Compliance:** Mandatory (`agents-mandatory.mdc`). Applies to all Kotlin changes.

## Stack (pin in `gradle/libs.versions.toml`)

| Area | Version / library |
|------|-------------------|
| Kotlin | 2.3.21 |
| Compose Multiplatform | 1.8.0 |
| AGP | 9.2.1 |
| Koin | 4.0.2 |
| Coroutines | 1.10.2 |
| Supabase Kotlin | 3.5.0 (auth, postgrest, realtime, functions) |
| Ktor | 3.4.0 |
| kotlinx-serialization | 1.8.1 |
| kotlinx-datetime | 0.6.1 |
| multiplatform-settings | 1.1.1 |

**Not in use:** Voyager (in catalog only), SQLDelight (catalog only). Do not add Voyager navigation without an explicit migration plan.

## Architecture & packages

- Base: `app.mymultiverse.kmp`
- `domain/` → `data/` → `presentation/` (see `architecture-clean.mdc`)
- Single module: `:composeApp`

## Navigation (custom, not Voyager)

- `AppRoute` sealed class: `Home`, `HouseholdMembers`, `Nutrition(section, aiMode)`
- `AppNavigator`: `navigateTo`, `replaceCurrent`, `navigateBack`, `canGoBack`
- `App.kt`: auth gate → `AnimatedContent` over routes; `BackHandler` for stack back
- Screen models: plain Koin-injected classes (`*ScreenModel`), not Voyager `ScreenModel`

## Concurrency & platform

- `kotlinx-coroutines` only; no platform threads in shared code.
- `expect`/`actual` for: haptics, auth deeplinks, language manager, personal export, push tokens.

## UI & resources

- Compose: `org.jetbrains.compose` + Material 3.
- Strings/drawables: `Res.string.*` / `Res.drawable.*` from `composeResources` — never Android `R.string` in shared UI.
- Theme: wrap screens in `AppTheme` (system light/dark).
- i18n: `i18n-multilingual.mdc`; format in composables, not screen models.

## DI (Koin)

- Register in `presentation/di/AppModule.kt` + `PlatformModule.kt` (android/ios).
- Inject repositories/services into screen models; composables use `koinInject()` for screen models or receive callbacks.
- Tests: `koin-test` + fakes in `commonTest/.../presentation/di/`.

## Logging

- Kermit for shared logging; map sensitive data before logging.

## When upgrading dependencies

- Check official docs (index in Cursor Settings → Docs); run full unit + instrumented compile after bump.
- Supabase client changes: verify auth session, realtime, and RPC calls against staging.
